dcterms:description: A dataset containing high-resolution scans of approximately 90 percent of Bach's compositions, providing the clearest representation of how Bach intended his music to be performed.
dcterms:title: Bach Digital

dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of 60 chorales by Bach, providing a textual representation of his work, including pitch classes, meter information, and human-annotated chord labels.
dcterms:title: Bach Choral Harmony dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset of lead sheets covering a significant portion of Bach's violin compositions, providing a concise representation of melodies with annotations for harmony and musical style.
